        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 1:01PM CDT by NWS Shreveport LA</headline>
        <description>At 101 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking an area of strong
thunderstorms 9 miles northeast of Manchester, or 19 miles north of
Clarksville, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Idabel, Broken Bow, Manchester, Wright City, Valliant, Millerton,
Garvin, Golden, Farmers Hill, Holly Creek, Glover, Oak Hill,
Albion, Silver City, Redland, Bryarly, Slim, Negley and Kiomatia.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
